8:
What's the matter? Is that "all you've
got?!"
41:
Can't hold back after all, can you?
Not when there's a tasty morsel
dangling right in front of your face.
45:
Try as you will to hide it—I see you.
You and I... We're nothing but
mindless animals!
50:
No, Betrane, we aren't. You just wish
that's what you were.
59:
You want so badly to be something
you're not. So you struggle... And it's
tearing you apart.
62:
And in the end... there's nothing
more human than that.
70:
Did you think I couldn't see the pain
you were in?
75:
Don't you DARE pretend to
understand me! As if YOU'D ever
understand what it's like to be at
your side!
79:
What kind of a sad joke would I be if
someone like you figured me out?
Can you even think of something
more pitiful?!
83: ...I have never pitied you. Not once.
86:
Respect, jealousy, yearning, hate,
violent impulses... Regardless of
what you may have thought, I'm no
stranger to any of these feelings.
89:
All these things are part of who I
am—but I won't let them control me.
94:
You're one tough bastard... The
strongest I've ever known.
99:
...I hope you never need to feel how I
feel, King.
108:
Target A neutralized. Engaging
target B.
115: GET THE HELL AWAY FROM HIM!
126:
*cough* Ow... Don't shake me like
that... There's not much we can do
now.
129:
Do whatever you want... with the
data... *sputter* Consider it... a
parting gift... Heh...
134:
What were you thinking?! You can't
throw your life away for something
like this!
138:
Heh... Pretty stupid, right? I couldn't
resist... After all, I'm just some
third-rate fixer...
141:
I'm not like you, King... I knew we
wouldn't be able to walk the same
path forever.
145: No, don't say things like that—
150:
You'll have to find your own jobs
from now on, partner...
154:
I never had what it takes... I was
never strong enough to rule this
world beside you.
158:
No! That's not true, Betrane! You
were—
162: I'm so sorry... I let you down.
169:
N-no... Betrane, please! I need you
by my side. Without you, I-I...
179:
He never let anyone tell him what to
do—especially not me. Betrane was
a free spirit until the very end.
181:
But his doubts and fears kept piling
up until he convinced himself he
wasn't good enough... and got
himself killed for it.
185:
So in the end, you used the data he
gave you to bring PBC to where it is
now?
189:
I sure did. And at that time, one of
my most reliable contacts was none
other than your mentor.
193:
So if I'm understanding correctly,
you decided to found your company
to fulfill your friend's last wish?
196:
But if you really were aiming for the
top... clearly, things didn't go so well.
Why?
200:
It's my way of proving him
wrong—that he was strong after all.
That I needed him all along.
203:
People don't need to become
animals to be strong. Our power to
choose our path forward... That's
true strength.
206:
No matter how unglamorous that
path might be... or how small your
office ends up being.
210:
Is that why you saw potential in
Nate?
214:
I could see the strength she carried
and her constant drive to improve.
No matter how many times she fell,
she never let that break her.
217:
So, I'll admit... I guess I am using her,
in a way. But helping her grow is far
more important to me than "being
on the top."
222: I'm back, boss! Ugh, what a day...
226:
Patrol duty is way tougher than it
sounds...
231:
Great work, you two! Keep it
up—passion is the key to success!
236:
Whoa, what's with the new look?
Yikes... You look like you could take
down a whole army!
239:
And how long have you been here,
Themis? Were you two... alone?
What're you plotting this time?
244:
Hey, now... King Johnson was just
telling me some old tales of his glory
days.
255:
Oh, come on! I was a young buck
once, too, y'know. I've got tons of
adventures left to share!
259:
Ooh, sounds juicy. Invetra's got time,
too. So let's hear it.
262:
Whoops, guess not. Just got an
emergency dispatch to the
commercial district.
264:
Uh oh... Stinelle's already on the
scene. I've got a bad feeling about
this...
269:
Oh gimme me a break... I just got
back!
278:
Time to get to work, gang! Crime
waits for no one!
282:
There won't be a soul in Qualia City
that doesn't know the power of PBC!
288:
...It's all thanks to you, partner.
Rest easy.
